courses.learning_outcomes:
Students will be able to:

* identify and explain the technological importance of genomics and bioinformatics in translational research;
* describe the analytical and experimental principles of Translational Genomics and its applied fields;
* apply the principles to address biomedical questions in a translational and clinical setting;
* compare and relate the selected topics and generate conceptual links between different research fields in order to establish a broader perspective.
* understand ethical issues, legal requirements and policies related to the use of genomics and AI in research and clinical applications.
